Symptoms of gastrointestinal upset can include:

1) Halitosis (bad breath);   
2) Loss of appetite;   
3) Gain of weight;   
4) Heartburn;   
5) Altered perception of taste;   
6) Pressure pain during climb;   
7) Desire for certain food types;   
8) Gastric and duodenal ulcers;   
9) Loss of weight.
